    <note type="biography">
        <p>Author and literary critic. Fellow, Trinity Hall, Cambridge, 1854–67; tutor, 1856–62. Left Cambridge for London in 1864 to pursue a literary career. Contributed articles to newspapers and journals on a wide variety of subjects. Editor of the <hi rend="italic">Cornhill Magazine</hi>, 1871–82. First editor of the <hi rend="italic">Dictionary of national biography</hi> from 1882. Knighted, 1902.</p></note>
